# ── RealDoor environment template ────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy what you need into frontend/.env.local (gitignored — Next.js reads env
# from the frontend/ folder, not the repo root). NEVER commit a real .env*:
# the root .gitignore blocks them, only this .env.example is tracked.
#
# Rule of thumb:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_*  → shipped to the browser. Public values only.
#   everything else → server-side only (API routes / engine). Real secrets
#                     live in Vercel env vars (vercel env add), never in git.

# ── Supabase (public by design — anon-equivalent; safe to share) ──────────
# These are also hardcoded as fallbacks in frontend/lib/supabase.ts, so the
# app runs with zero setup; set them here only to override (e.g. a personal
# Supabase project for local experiments).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://zgfanoruqwftbqhhvtwg.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_ThFBIsq2HyTAGwuWgdVuNw_bvfUh6Vy

# ── Server-side secrets (future engine / API routes) ──────────────────────
# Uncomment and fill locally when the corresponding feature lands.
# NO NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix here, ever — that would expose them to the browser.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=   # dashboard → Project Settings → API keys. Bypasses RLS: server only.

# ── Supabase Edge Function secrets (set in the dashboard, not this file) ──
# Dashboard → Project Settings → Edge Functions → Secrets.
# These values belong to the deployed `understand-chat` function and must
# never be prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ or copied into frontend/.env.local.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
